CatDescriptText: Mrs. Susie Kelley, housewife, Wick Street and Mr. Antonio Duncan, cleaner and presser, North Side, were part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 17, 1962, pg. 7 with question: "What's wrong with the Republican party in Allegheny County?" Mrs. Susie Kelley's answer reads: "I couldn't say anything much because I'm a Democrat.  I think that everything is wrong with the Republican Party."  Mr. Antonio Duncan's answer reads: "I think that we should have a two-party system, but I'm not that much interested in the Republican troubles because we Democrats are doing all right and our man is in office."
TitMainTitle: Two frames: Portrait of Susie Kelley wearing dark fur collared coat and hat with bow, standing in front of Jenkins Arcade, Liberty Avenue, Downtown; Portrait of Antonio Duncan wearing textured coat, plaid scarf, and hat, standing in front of Jenkins Arcade, Liberty Avenue, Downtown
